description: Frank Robbins' masterpiece, one of the all-time greatest action/adventure newspaper comic strips, Johnny Hazard, returns with volume three of the series! Continuing the adventures of Johnny Hazard and Brandy picking up the storyline where volume one left off. See more trend-setting artwork by comics legend Frank Robbins in one of the most important adventure strips to ever grace newspapers. Reproduced entirely from the original King Features press proofs.
name: Volume Three: 1947-1949

description: This multiple award-winning comic magazine features the hilarious misadventures of a group of gamers (the Knights) and their friends, along with useful role-playing and other articles for gamers, from a gamer's perspective. It's a slice of (fantasy) life in strips, articles, reviews and features, and a wonderful celebration of the gaming culture!

Isobel Blades, First Lady, pays a visit to Congressman Chris Higgins, a former love interest rumored to be plotting Stephen's impeachment. In the asteroid belt, the purpose of the Chandelier becomes clear, as it powers up for the first time. Earth's solar system will never be the same.

After a chance encounter at sea, fisherman Mishka washes ashore on an uncharted island. Surrounded by monsters and worse, can Mishka survive long enough to solve the mystery of the Sea Devil and return home?

Set before the Civil War, Pariah, Missouri is a frontier riverboat town and a haven for evil. Hiram Buchanan, a Pinkerton spy, uncovers a crime syndicate and manipulates a misfit team to follow him into danger, where the supernatural is all around them. Buffy the Vampire Slayer meets Deadwood.
name: GN

description: In this prequel to Planet Gigantic, two genetically engineered teenagers and their robot caretaker MOTHER are sent into uncharted areas of space to collect scientific data. What they find is far more dangerous than mineral deposits.

THIS MONTH'S COVER ART: New projects from IDW and DC!

THIS MONTH'S THEME: Holiday Gift Giving Ideas!

PREVIEWS is your ultimate guide to all of the comics, graphic novels and po-cutlure merchandise available from your local comic book shop... revealed up to two months in advance! Hundreds of comics and graphic novels from the best comic publishers; the coolest toys and pop-culture merchandise on Earth; plus PREVIEWS exclusive items available nowhere else! Now more than ever, PREVIEWS is here to show the tales, toys and treasures in your future! This September issue features items scheduled to ship in November 2014 and beyond.

The Saint encounters adrenaline junkie Miles Hallin. Hallin claims to be able to cheat death, but when one of Templar's friends is killed, the Saint decides to put that to the test. A classic Leslie Charteris novel adapted to a graphic novel!
name: GN

volume.name: The Saint: The Man Who Wouldn't Die

description: Let's face it, getting real flesh and blood girls to put up with uncomfortable positions and too-tight ropes can get annoying, expensive, and, in some states, arrested! But when all you're using is a Number 2 pencil and some truly inspired cunning, nobody gets hurt and everyone has a fun time!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Sensual Distress: The Art of Steve O. Reno

description: In the "real" world, you take a few dozen young ladies and put them in all sorts of uncomfortable and sexually provocative positions - you're gonna get a visit from your local law enforcement agency! How much better it is to let Steve O Reno do all the heavy lifting in this second volume of erotic discomfort!
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Sensual Distress: The Art of Steve O. Reno

description:
Jishin (Confidence): 14 year-old ninja princess Shianndrea Toshigawa and her strike team have a new mission: spy on their rivals, the Azumi Ninja Clan, and discover what secret dealings they have with the evil Emperor of Japan. But when the plan goes awry and fellow ninja Hamasuke is captured, can Shianndrea overcome her lack of confidence and save him before it's too late?

The Six, when brought together under the right circumstances, can destroy the whole of the world. Now, the most vile of creatures--Griselda the Grey Mother--has claimed all of the weapons for herself. Using the guns, she'll call down endless darkness and remake reality in her own monstrous image! The end of the world is nigh!
name: Hell and High Water Part One

description: Collecting the complete, two-volume SteamPunk epic future of the World of Oz! A century after the Wicked Witch was killed, The Emerald City is ruled by a once-revered hero, an ice-witch rules over the north, the Lions overrun the forests, evil twins approach from the West, and secrets hide in every shadow. Salvation for Oz comes from the unlikely young Victoria Wright. She comes to find that the smallest of actions can have much larger implications, and the most insignificant of us can change the world. Collects The Steam Engines of Oz FCBD, The Steam Engines of Oz #1-3, and The Steam Engines of Oz: The Geared Leviathan #1-3.
name: HC

volume.name: The Steam Engines of Oz: Hardcover Collection

description: Master French cartoonist Yvan Pommaux introduces a wealth of historically accurate details that immerse readers in the context and culture of ancient Greece. The story is supplemented with character cards, maps, mazes, and an index of cited names that will keep readers coming back for more! The literary quality of this book will appeal to readers young and old, making it an excellent addition to every classroom and library.
name: GN

description: Growing up, Liz Prince wasn't a girly girl, dressing in pink tutus or playing Pretty Pretty princess like the other girls in her neighborhood. But she wasn't exactly one of the guys either, as she quickly learned when her Little League baseball coach exiled her to the outfield instead of letting her take the pitcher's mound. Liz was somewhere in the middle, and Tomboy is the story of her struggle to find the place where she belonged. A memoir told anecdotally, Tomboy follows author and zine artist Liz Prince through her early childhood into adulthood and explores her ever-evolving struggles and wishes regarding what it means to "be a girl."
name: GN

description:
Eisner Award winners Mark Evanier and Sergio Aragons team with the incomparable Thomas Yeates for a crossover thousands of years in the making. Groo vs. Conan pits the two most feared barbarians in comics against one another. Will the savagery of Conan overwhelm the stupidity of Groo, or will Groos unmatched aptitude for destruction catch the Cimmerian swordsman off guard?

Comics greatest barbarians together at last!
name: Chapter Two

description: From renowned UK comics writer Pat Mills and legendary artist Joe Colquhoun comes a truly classic piece of British comics history, by turns thrilling, humorous and horrifying. In 1916, Charley Bourne enlists to fight on the battlefields of France and finds himself swept up by bloody horror and needless sacrifice in the trenches of the First World War. Collected now in a bumper paperback omnibus format, an ideal jumping-on point for new readers. This collects the original episodes #1-87.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Crossed have taken everything from humanity - civilization, dignity, and hope are all gone in an instant. And in their disease riddled homicidal brains, their mission will never end until the last of the uninfected are writing in pain. How can you survive in a world gone mad? You don't... JUSTIN JORDAN proves that in a world of maniacs there is no hope. There is only the Crossed.

Available with Regular and Red Crossed Incentive covers by Christian Zanier,Torture cover by Tim Vigil, Wraparound cover by Rafa Ortiz, and Fatal Fantasy cover by Matt Martin.

Painter and cartoonist Tom Neelys first graphic novel, The Blot, is like a sad song that breaks your heart while reminding you of lifes beauty.

The Blot follows a nameless everyman who, while dealing with the fallout from a doomed relationship, is stalked by a mysterious black splotch. As the story unfolds, this shape-shifting blot appears as a harmless cloud of ink, a faceless demon, a source of strength and an inescapable darkness, testing our character in a new way with each metamorphosis.

Submerged Part 1

With the death of another Toxic Fruit soldier, the organization is at a breaking point. Lose any more agents and they might not be able to hold the line against the demonic threat.

Tart and two of her colleagues are pulled from the front lines and sent on a survival training mission, while their boss travels to the outskirts of Hell to barter with a Devil.
name: Submerged Part 1

description:
Chapter Two

The mystery continues as Santiago + Dunbar descend into the depths of Subhattan!
name: Scale the Earth Part Two

description: Following a stalemate with the Green Hornet and Kato, Batman and Robin pursue the valuable coins stolen from the Gotham Bank. But are the coins bait for another trap?
name: The Treacherous Snare Part 2

description:
Things begin to coalesce as Blastosaurus, Naomi and, the now captured, Teeth arrive at the haunted house. But something else has turned up too, something unknown that is stalking the children. Can Blastosaurus rescue them, catch Harry and, most importantly, survive the strange shifting reality of the house?

Remember, something's coming and there are only 13 bullets left.
It all comes down to this. The clock is ticking and there's one last run. Who will make it back to Turbo Pizza first?

Those rascals are at it again! This time they'll be investigating a haunting, taking on a troublesome raccoon and getting jacked up on too much coffee! All this and much more in the latest page of CAAATS!
The action adventures continues with "Dirk Benedict in the 25th Century".

Sigh

In which Carol walks. A lot.
name: Sigh

description:
The Age of Darkness continues as the evil Dark Queen and her husband rule over Earth. Humanity is learning why she is called the Dark Queen. People are dying by the thousands, all for her pleasure. Meanwhile, the few humans and Realm Knights left to oppose her are scattered in the ruins of what was once New York City. But she will not rest until they are all dead or enslaved. And she has just the new weapon to aid her in her quest... the Child of Darkness.

Kevin and Matt meet a kid who may be more dangerous than the adults trying to kill them!

Our young hero and last hope for peace has been captured by Baron Kah Lee.

Trapped, outmatched, and alone the young ape kings life is not the only thing at stake.

If Pale cannot overcome Kah Lee and neutralize the Citadel, nothing will stand in his way of dominating and oppressing the rest of animal kind.
name: Rise of the Ape King Chapter Six

The Great Game

In Modern London, James, Wendy and Irfan hide out from The Eternal Children.

Over a century ago, Cap'n James battles Skraelings and Lost Boys.
name: The Great Game

description:
The plan has gone terribly wrong, and the Mermaids have declared war upon Mankind. Lunita must face them and stop the massacre - even by paying with her own life if it is needed! The fantastic run of the daughter of the Moon concludes with a shocking finale!

Note: The digital edition (8/27/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Friends

Who is this mysterious new woman, and who wants her dead? What does Vella find in Morris' apartment? M3 is back, and her story continues. With cover artwork by Nouri Zander and Jayel Draco.
name: Friends

description:
We're Gonna Do This One Of Two Ways

Here come the girls.
name: We're Gonna Do This One Of Two Ways

description: Each issue of Marvel Previews is a comic book-sized, 120-page, full-color guide and preview to all of Marvel's upcoming releases - it's your #1 source for advanced information on Marvel Comics! This September issue features items scheduled to ship in November 2014 and beyond.

What started as a night of stargazing becomes a close encounter with an extraterrestrial being! Is he a friend or foe, and what does he want with Alden and the rest of us Earthlings? First, what does he eat?

Sonny meets with Pasqual's men as a rocket launch foils Tubbs and Zito's chance at recording the conversation. They soon realize that the meet is a setup, as Federal Agent Phineas betrays them. Tubbs and Zito subdue Phineas but it's too late: Pasqual's men have kidnapped Sonny. Tubbs jumps behind the wheel of Crockett's beloved Spyder and races to the rescue.

A young boy is recruited off the streets by an unknown benefactor and manipulated into starting a plot that will last for nearly two decades. His value to this agenda grows over time, and soon he becomes the infamous Zero. Secrets are revealed and identities made known as the story's climactic confrontation is set up...
Four teenagers face an amazing and dangerous reality when mysteriously granted the super powers they made up as children.

Crazy Dave sends his niece Patrice and her headstrong pal Nate into the future. What do future zombies eat for breakfast? How do you get a Zombie Jetpack Control Manual? And who are the two most dangerous criminals of the post-2020 period? Well, our two young adventurers are about to learn the answer to one of those questions! As they race to beat Zomboss before the zombie leader can recover all the parts he needs to rebuild his wicked Sun Vacuum, our heroes must thwart Zombosss nefarious future schemes in order to protect all eras of humanity! Paul Tobin (Bandette, Prometheus) and Ron Chan (The Guild, Husbands) deliver the exciting fourth chapter in their Plants vs. Zombies: Timepocalypse series!

Dark Horse Digitals second run of Plants vs. Zombies comics!

A humor-filled romp for all ages!

Tobin and Chan take us on another original PvZ adventure!

All-new Plants vs. Zombie's comic-book series!

Brains? If you have them, wed like to invite you on this . . . most delicious adventure.Dr. Zomboss

In this issue, Patrice and Nate visit the future in search of more sun vacuum parts. Except now, they have aged into their adult selves. Patrice is now a master martial artist, and Nate is a scientist.

With their newly-advanced skills, they defeat the zombies of the future and get the part. Zomboss is now seriously annoyed.

As death threatens every person he cares about in the world, Robin must push himself past his absolute limits to rescue them all. Does the young rogue have what it takes to save everybody or will someones life fall through the cracks?

The villainous mastermind Doctor Nihilist has eradicated the heroes with his Destructo-Ray, but is quickly losing control over his newly conquered Earth. The deadly fall-out from his super-weapon of mass destruction has mutated into a poison that threatens all life, while the woman Nihilist loves has joined forces with his greatest enemy, Masked Champion...who she quickly learns is powerless against the impending Armageddon...
name: Act II

description: When Circe attacks the human defenders of Washington DC, Wonder Woman must win a battle without harming her attackers. But is there more going on than even she can see?
name: Defender of Truth

description:
Strangeness

After Xigi's rejection, Ariel thought that she was done with these magic stuff. But who shows up at school? Zoe and another hot boy who just happens to be a craft user.
name: Strangeness

description:
Crisis of the Cerulean King Part 3

Pythro faces the wrath of the Cerulean King in this soul shattering conclusion!
name: Crisis of the Cerulean King Part 3

description:
First Kill

Wyatt Stone starts to crack from memories of his past. Events at home push Stone to take a big step over the edge. Things will never be the same for him or those around him.
name: First Kill

description: With another attack in the park, it seems as if the police have arrested the wrong man. But the latest victim may hold the clue to who the identity of the murderer.

Kept at Bay

The vampires had more aces up their sleeve then Ethan Ronald expected.

Now, wounded with his tail between his legs, the vampires strike once again.

But who is the greater monster?
name: Kept At Bay

description:
Talking gorillas. Knights and dragons. Mazes and minotaurs. Why does Daniel Bryan keep insisting they were all part of a WWE Monday Night Raw gone completely out of control? With their jobs at stake, Rey Mysterio and CM Punk must help Bryan make sense of his sword and sorcery fantasy memories to uncover who or what was actually responsible for all of them going bananas. And speaking of bananas, that talking gorilla proves to be all too real when it attacks Mysterio in a David versus Goliath confrontation of great ape proportions.

description: With the annexation of R'Cani fast approaching, Deron, Zorg and Z'Arr come up with a plan to free Cody of his spell and stop General Zolak. The only problem? It might take a while...

Its time for a thrilling conclusion to the current storyline of Batman/Superman, as two Batmen and two Supermen try to stop the machinations of the trickster god Kaiyo! Meanwhile, in Injustice: Gods Among Us, its the god of War, Ares, whos causing problems for Wonder Woman, while the King of Atlantis, Aquaman, make his presence felt at sea. Last of all, if you've ever wondered how Darkseid became the world-killing threat he is now, prepare yourself for his origin story, right here in this issue!
